233
00:29:23,972 --> 00:29:26,517
The twins have been torturing me. Look.

234
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:27,935
How awful.

235
00:29:31,063 --> 00:29:32,397
Chinese burns.

236
00:29:33,982 --> 00:29:35,943
That's right.

237
00:29:36,276 --> 00:29:41,114
They want to go home.
They think it's me that's keeping them here.

238
00:29:46,954 --> 00:29:48,330
Lola.

239
00:29:49,039 --> 00:29:53,418
Can I tell you something?
Something really terrible.

240
00:29:53,502 --> 00:29:54,795
Yes, please.

241
00:29:55,629 --> 00:29:58,757
What's the worst word
you can possibly imagine?

242
00:30:09,351 --> 00:30:11,603
-He's a sex maniac!
-That's right.

243
00:30:11,687 --> 00:30:13,188
-What's Cecilia going to do?
-I don't know.

244
00:30:13,272 --> 00:30:15,858
-You ought to call the police.
-Do you think so?

245
00:30:15,941 --> 00:30:18,652
He said he thought about it all day long.

246
00:30:18,735 --> 00:30:20,904
All you have to do is show them the letter.

247
00:30:20,988 --> 00:30:23,782
-You won't tell anyone, will you, promise?
-I promise.

248
00:30:23,866 --> 00:30:27,077
Good. If he found out,
there's no knowing what he might do.

249
00:30:27,161 --> 00:30:28,370
You're right.

250
00:30:30,622 --> 00:30:33,917
You better tidy your face.
I've still got to change.

251
00:30:36,253 --> 00:30:38,839
Thanks, Briony. You're a real brick.

252
00:33:00,314 --> 00:33:01,440
Cecilia!

253
00:33:19,666 --> 00:33:22,127
-It was a mistake.
-Briony read it.

254
00:33:22,419 --> 00:33:24,671
My God, I'm so sorry.
It was the wrong version.

255
00:33:24,755 --> 00:33:26,048
Yes.

256
00:33:29,885 --> 00:33:31,970
-It was never meant to be read.
-No.

257
00:34:07,256 --> 00:34:08,841
What was in the version
I was meant to read?

258
00:34:08,924 --> 00:34:10,884
I don't know. It was more formal. Less...

259
00:34:10,968 --> 00:34:12,594
-Anatomical?
-Yes.

260
00:34:19,226 --> 00:34:23,438
It's been there for weeks,
and then this morning by the fountain...

261
00:34:32,739 --> 00:34:35,617
I've never done anything like that before.

262
00:34:35,951 --> 00:34:38,912
And I was so angry with you,
and with myself.

263
00:34:41,748 --> 00:34:45,252
I thought if you went away to medical
school, then I'd be happy, but...

264
00:34:45,335 --> 00:34:48,922
I don't know how I could have been
so ignorant about myself, so...

265
00:34:52,843 --> 00:34:54,386
So stupid.

266
00:35:01,101 --> 00:35:03,937
You do know what I'm talking about,
don't you?

267
00:35:06,607 --> 00:35:09,443
You knew before I did.

268
00:35:11,111 --> 00:35:12,946
Why are you crying?

269
00:35:14,490 --> 00:35:16,116
Don't you know?

270
00:35:16,617 --> 00:35:18,368
Yes, I know exactly.

271
00:37:02,681 --> 00:37:03,765
Robbie.

272
00:37:04,725 --> 00:37:05,809
Cecilia.

273
00:37:07,728 --> 00:37:08,854
I love you.

274
00:37:11,398 --> 00:37:12,774
I love you.

275
00:37:53,941 --> 00:37:55,609
Someone's come in.

276
00:37:57,277 --> 00:37:58,529
Cecilia!

277
00:38:42,573 --> 00:38:44,533
People were sitting out
having dinner on the pavement.

278
00:38:44,616 --> 00:38:49,037
It was always the view of my parents
that hot weather encouraged loose morals.

279
00:38:49,121 --> 00:38:51,498
In high summer, my sister and l
were never allowed out of the house.

280
00:38:51,582 --> 00:38:55,294
They thought the villagers would be
unnecessarily provoked.

281
00:38:57,212 --> 00:39:01,091
What do you say, Cee? Does the hot weather
make you behave badly?

282
00:39:02,885 --> 00:39:05,846
-Good heavens, you're blushing.
-It's just hot in here, that's all.

283
00:39:05,929 --> 00:39:08,515
Lola, wipe that lipstick off.
You're far too young.

284
00:39:08,599 --> 00:39:12,311
What about you, Briony?
What sins have you committed today?

285
00:39:13,187 --> 00:39:16,481
-I've done nothing wrong.
Have you seen the twins recently?

286
00:39:16,607 --> 00:39:19,276
They didn't look very happy
last time I saw them, poor little chaps.

287
00:39:19,359 --> 00:39:22,738
You know nothing about it.
-Briony. I can't imagine what's got into you.

288
00:39:22,821 --> 00:39:25,365
-I've never known you to be so rude.
Well, they're not poor little chaps.

289
00:39:25,449 --> 00:39:27,576
-Just look what they did to Lola.
-What are you talking about?

290
00:39:27,659 --> 00:39:30,871
Jackson and Pierrot
bruised her arm. Gave her Chinese burns.

291
00:39:30,954 --> 00:39:32,873
I'm afraid she's quite right.
I had to pull them off her.

292
00:39:32,956 --> 00:39:35,292
How I got my war wound.

293
00:39:35,375 --> 00:39:36,793
The twins did that, Lola?

294
00:39:36,877 --> 00:39:38,754
Yes, it all turned
into a bit of a wrestle,

295
00:39:38,837 --> 00:39:41,173
