-Yes, it was him.

318
00:42:50,112 --> 00:42:51,697
Lola, who was it?

319
00:42:53,824 --> 00:42:57,286
It was Robbie, wasn't it? Robbie?

320
00:42:59,079 --> 00:43:01,748
-You saw him?
-Like you said, he's a sex maniac.

321
00:43:01,832 --> 00:43:04,585
And you don't even know
what happened before dinner.

322
00:43:04,668 --> 00:43:06,253
I caught him attacking my sister
in the library.

323
00:43:06,336 --> 00:43:08,547
I don't know what he'd have done
if I hadn't come in.

324
00:43:08,630 --> 00:43:12,092
-You actually saw him?
-Of course I did. Plain as day.

325
00:43:13,927 --> 00:43:18,223
He pushed me to the ground.
And then he put his hands over my eyes.

326
00:43:19,391 --> 00:43:24,479
-I couldn't actually... I never actually...
-Listen. I've known him

327
00:43:24,563 --> 00:43:26,773
my whole life, and I saw him.

328
00:43:27,566 --> 00:43:29,943
Because I couldn't say for sure.

329
00:43:30,777 --> 00:43:33,489
Well, I can. And I will.

330
00:43:38,285 --> 00:43:41,872
Call the police.
And she'll be needing a doctor, as well.

331
00:43:52,799 --> 00:43:57,095
-It's all right, dear. It's all right now.
Is Robbie back yet?

332
00:43:57,179 --> 00:43:59,389
I haven't seen him.

333
00:43:59,806 --> 00:44:01,642
I know who it was.

334
00:44:04,102 --> 00:44:07,564
-You saw him, then?
-Yes, I saw him.

335
00:44:07,648 --> 00:44:10,692
-Just as you see me?
-I know it was him.

336
00:44:10,776 --> 00:44:14,154
You know it was him? Or you saw him?

337
00:44:15,489 --> 00:44:18,992
-Yes, I did, I saw him.
-With your own eyes?

338
00:44:19,993 --> 00:44:23,789
Yes. I saw him, I saw him with my own eyes.

339
00:44:27,751 --> 00:44:29,336
Well done, darling.

340
00:45:20,929 --> 00:45:24,433
My brother and I found the two of them
down by the lake.

341
00:45:24,516 --> 00:45:26,643
You didn't see anyone else?

342
00:45:28,854 --> 00:45:33,567
I wouldn't necessarily believe everything
Briony tells you. She's rather fanciful.

343
00:45:41,783 --> 00:45:44,912
When they went looking,
I went up to my dad's.

344
00:45:44,995 --> 00:45:47,623
-I did, honest.
Why was that?

345
00:45:48,916 --> 00:45:50,667
To tell him all about it.

346
00:45:52,711 --> 00:45:56,256
-I know I shouldn't have opened it.
No, you should not.

347
00:45:57,758 --> 00:46:00,719
But at least you've done the right thing now.

348
00:46:39,800 --> 00:46:42,010
Sir, there is someone coming.

349
00:47:11,248 --> 00:47:13,083
-Time you went to bed.
-But...

350
00:47:13,167 --> 00:47:14,293
Now.

351
00:48:27,282 --> 00:48:28,367
Cecilia!

352
00:48:51,640 --> 00:48:56,270
You liars! You liars! Liars! Liars!

353
00:49:36,185 --> 00:49:38,353
Northern France
Four years later

354
00:49:43,859 --> 00:49:47,362
I says to him, I says, "You can sit
down there, twiddling your thumbs,

355
00:49:47,446 --> 00:49:49,531
"waiting to get your head blown off,
if you want to.

356
00:49:49,615 --> 00:49:50,782
"I'm off out of it."

357
00:50:00,459 --> 00:50:04,421
Bonsoir monsieur. Bonsoir?
Let me do this.

358
00:50:19,645 --> 00:50:21,063
What's his game?

359
00:50:21,146 --> 00:50:23,440
-He says he's got something for us.
-Fucking hell!

360
00:50:24,775 --> 00:50:26,985
Wait! We have food for you

361
00:50:27,110 --> 00:50:28,237
Bread, sugar

362
00:50:28,320 --> 00:50:29,404
And wine!

363
00:50:39,790 --> 00:50:41,458
What are you doing here?

364
00:50:47,714 --> 00:50:51,260
When the retreat started, Panzers attacked,

365
00:50:52,261 --> 00:50:54,429
and I was separated from my unit

366
00:50:54,596 --> 00:50:57,099
So it's true, the English are retreating

367
00:50:59,935 --> 00:51:02,604
We'll be gone at first light

368
00:51:04,148 --> 00:51:07,025
We fought all those years,
lost all those dead,

369
00:51:07,484 --> 00:51:09,987
now the Germans are in France again

370
00:51:13,532 --> 00:51:14,950
We will come back

371
00:51:17,119 --> 00:51:18,787
we will throw them out

372
00:51:20,622 --> 00:51:23,417
I promise you

373
00:51:24,793 --> 00:51:26,461
Good luck

374
00:51:31,466 --> 00:51:32,843
Come on, then.

375
00:51:32,926 --> 00:51:36,930
How come a toff like you, talks French
and everything, ends up a private?

376
00:51:37,014 --> 00:51:40,642
Not eligible for officers' training
if you join direct from prison.

377
00:51:40,809 --> 00:51:44,062
-You're pulling my tit.
-No, I'm not.

378
00:51:45,647 --> 00:51:49,109
They gave me a choice.
Stay in prison or join the Army.

379
00:51:50,152 --> 00:51:53,322
And for the record,
the last thing I am is a toff.

380
00:52:12,299 --> 00:52:14,343
Six months earlier

381
00:52:41,537 --> 00:52:43,038
I'm sorry I'm late, I got lost.

382
00:52:43,163 --> 00:52:44,915
-Hello.
-Hello.

383
00:52:54,675 --> 00:52:57,219
-Should we sit down?
-Yes, of course.

384
00:53:12,317 --> 00:53:15,487
-I'm sorry, I can't remember, l...
-Two. Thank you.

385
00:53:50,063 --> 00:53:51,940
Where are you living?

386
00:53:53,609 --> 00:53:55,944
Tiny flat in Balham. It's ghastly.

387
00:53:56,028 --> 00:53:59,323
-The landlady's rude and horribly nosy.
-You look the same.

388
00:53:59,406 --> 00:54:01,909
-Apart from the uniform, of course.
-Yes, I'm sorry. I've got to go back

389
00:54:01,992 --> 00:54:05,120
-to the hospital in half an hour.
-Oh, God, that...

390
00:54:26,475 --> 00:54:27,893
-Sorry.
-No.

391
00:54:32,022 --> 00:54:34,608
Have you been in touch with your family?

392
00:54:34,691 --> 00:54:36,735
No, I told you I wouldn't.

393
00:54:38,237 --> 00:54:40,614
Leon waited outside the hospital last week,
I just pushed past him.

394
00:54:40,697 --> 00:54:43,450
Cee, you don't owe me anything.

395
00:54:45,577 --> 00:54:48,205
Robbie, didn't you read my letters?

396
00:54:48,622 --> 00:54:50,833
Had I been allowed to visit you,
had they let me every day,

397
00:54:50,916 --> 00:54:53,418
-I would have been there every day.
-Yes, but...

398
00:54:53,502 --> 00:54:57,089
If all we have rests on a few moments

399
00:54:57,172 --> 00:54:59,758
in a library three and a half years ago,
then I'm not sure,

400
00:54:59,842 --> 00:55:02,970
-I don't know if...
-Robbie, look at me.

401
00:55:06,139 --> 00:55:08,767
Look at me.

402
00:55:09,852 --> 00:55:11,228
Come back.

403
00:55:14,439 --> 00:55:16,150
Come back to me.

404
00:55:30,414 --> 00:55:32,166
Dearest Cecilia.

405
00:55:33,876 --> 00:55:36,003
Dearest Cecilia.

406
00:55:43,260 --> 00:55:44,386
Cecilia.

407
00:55:59,902 --> 00:56:01,987
A friend of mine has a cottage by the coast.

408
00:56:02,070 --> 00:56:04,406
Said we can borrow it
when you're next on leave.

409
00:56:04,490 --> 00:56:07,618
White clapboard
with blue-painted window frames.

410
00:56:09,411 --> 00:56:12,789
-I hope this bus never comes.
-Here.

411
00:56:14,958 --> 00:56:17,794
Something to think of while you're away.

412
00:56:40,234 --> 00:56:41,360
I love you.

413
00:58:12,117 --> 00:58:14,286
Some poor sod's gonna catch a packet.

414
00:58:22,836 --> 00:58:27,090
My darling. Briony found
my address somehow, and sent a letter.

415
00:58:28,300 --> 00:58:31,053
The first surprise was
she didn't go up to Cambridge.

416
00:58:31,136 --> 00:58:33,931
She's doing nurse's training
at my old hospital.

417
00:58:35,140 --> 00:58:37,935
I think she may be doing this
as some kind of penance.

418
00:58:38,018 --> 00:58:42,731
She says she's beginning to get the full
grasp of what she did, and what it meant.

419
00:58:42,856 --> 00:58:45,359
She wants to come and talk to me.

420
00:58:46,693 --> 00:58:51,448
I love you. I'll wait for you. Come back.

421
00:58:52,866 --> 00:58:53,951
Come back to me.

422
00:58:55,285 --> 00:58:57,704
Come back. Come back to me.

423
00:58:58,747 --> 00:59:01,917
Come back. Come back to me.

424
00:59:05,337 --> 00:59:07,339
So where we going, guv?

425
00:59:22,062 --> 00:59:24,314
Fucking hate those boots!

426
00:59:24,398 --> 00:59:27,192
I hate them worse
than all the fucking Germans put together!

427
00:59:27,276 --> 00:59:30,445
You'll have a job getting back to England
in your socks.

428
01:01:08,210 --> 01:01:10,963
Come on, pal,
you should be getting dressed.

429
01:01:11,046 --> 01:01:14,216
-If I fell in, would you save me?
-Of course.

430
01:01:26,895 --> 01:01:27,938
Briony!

431
01:01:53,213 --> 01:01:54,381
Thank you.

432
01:02:02,681 --> 01:02:04,141
Thank you! Thank you, thank you!

433
01:02:04,224 --> 01:02:06,977
That's an incredibly bloody
stupid thing to do.

434
01:02:07,102 --> 01:02:08,479
I wanted you to save me.
-Don't you know

435
01:02:08,562 --> 01:02:10,230
how easily you could have drowned?

436
01:02:10,564 --> 01:02:13,400
-You saved me.
-Stupid child!

437
01:02:13,484 --> 01:02:17,321
You could have killed us both.
Is that your idea of a joke?

438
01:02:19,072 --> 01:02:21,783
I want to thank you for saving my life.

439
01:02:22,951 --> 01:02:25,579
I will be eternally grateful to you.

440
01:02:38,091 --> 01:02:39,968
